Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Renal function is impaired, as indicated by elevated creatinine. Lipid profile shows mildly increased LDL cholesterol, which may increase cardiovascular risk. All other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal impairment and consideration of cardiovascular risk management.
